Name: CST3-related cerebral amyloid angiopathy
Definition: A cerebral amyloid angiopathy that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of CST3 on chromosome 20p11.21.

Name: APP-related cerebral amyloid angiopathy
Definition: A cerebral amyloid angiopathy that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of APP on chromosome 21q21.3.

Name: ITM2B-related cerebral amyloid angiopathy 1
Definition: A cerebral amyloid angiopathy characterized by onset in the 4th to 6th decade of life

Name: ITM2B-related cerebral amyloid angiopathy 2
Definition: A cerebral amyloid angiopathy characterized by ataxia
